div></figure><p>Escalade IQ 将在公路上亮相，加入<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/hummer-ev-first-drive-an-enormous-electric-super-truck-133030316.html">悍马</a>、 <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chevrolet-silverado-ev-details-ces-debut-171551300.html">Silverado</a> 、 <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-officially-reveals-its-electrified-2024-gmc-sierra-denali-213601650.html">GMC Sierra Denali</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/stellantis-first-look-ram-1500-revolution-bev-concept-ces-2023-223035895.html">Ram 1500 EV</a>等电动庞然大物的行列。新款凯迪拉克长近 19 英尺，宽 8 英尺，高超过 6 英尺。但当第二排和第三排座椅折叠起来时，你的车内空间很大，载货量为 119.2 立方英尺。 （它还有一个后备箱，可额外增加 12 立方英尺的存储空间。）</p><p>总而言之，这款 SUV 的牵引力可达 8,000 磅。此外，它还配备了跨仪表板的 55 英寸双屏 LED 显示屏，其信息娱乐系统运行 Android Automotive OS（包括 Google Assistant、Google 地图和 Play 商店）。高端系列通过 AKG 40 扬声器阵列提供 360 度音频。</p><p> 2025 款 Escalade IQ 将于明年夏天在通用汽车位于底特律的零工厂装配中心开始生产。定价“起价约为 130,000 美元”，包括目的地费用。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/cadillacs-first-escalade-ev-has-a-450-mile-range-and-starts-at-130000-182816273.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/cadillacs-first-escalade-ev-has-a-450-mile-range-and-starts-at-130000-182816273.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> f72406eb-802b-43fa-8325-6a3c5e10841a</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:28:16 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691609780</ingested><modified> 2023-08-09T19:36:30+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="1072" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/e8aa8730-36e3-11ee-bf57-8d0734062ab4" width="1859"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1072" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/e8aa8730-36e3-11ee-bf57-8d0734062ab4" width="1859"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Cadillac]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Marketing photo for the 2025 Cadillac Escalade IQ. The silver SUV sits on a city street in front of brownstone buildings with skyscrapers in the background.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[2025 Cadillac Escalade IQ]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Epic loses bid to make Apple change its App Store payment rules right now]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/epic-games/"><ins>Epic Games</ins></a>试图迫使<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/apple/"><ins>苹果</ins></a>尽快改变其 App Store 支付方式，但失败了。这家<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/fortnite/"><em><ins>《堡垒之夜》</ins></em></a>制造商要求最高法院推翻美国第九巡回上诉法院的一项裁决，该裁决推迟了针对苹果应用商店规则的禁令。然而，据<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://news.bloomberglaw.com/us-law-week/apple-can-keep-app-store-rules-for-now-as-top-court-spurns-epic"><em><ins>彭博社</ins></em></a>报道，埃琳娜·卡根法官<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.supremecourt.gov/search.aspx?filename=/docket/docketfiles/html/public/23a78.html"><ins>拒绝了这一请求</ins></a>，没有提供任何解释<em>&nbsp;</em>报告。</p><p>第九巡回上诉法院最初于四月份<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-wins-appeals-court-ruling-against-epic-games-191331514.html"><ins>维持了该禁令</ins></a>。然而，它于 7 月暂停了该禁令，以便苹果可以<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-wants-to-take-the-epic-games-case-to-the-supreme-court-123501115.html"><ins>将此案提交至最高法院</ins></a>。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>在 2021 年苹果和 Epic Games 进行了一场轰动一时的审判后，一名下级法院法官<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-epic-games-lawsuit-ruling-app-store-153113436.html"><ins>裁定</ins></a>，苹果阻止第三方开发商引导用户选择其他支付选项，违反了加州的不公平竞争法。法官下令停止这种做法。</p><p>过去三年来，两家公司一直在 iOS 上的应用内支付问题上争论不休。 Epic 告诉移动<em>《堡垒之夜</em>》玩家，如果<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/epic-games-fortnite-direct-payment-discounts-143422257.html"><ins>绕过 iOS 和 Android 支付系统，</ins></a>他们将获得游戏内 V-Bucks 货币的折扣，这引起了苹果（和谷歌）的愤怒。苹果和谷歌在 iOS 和 Android 上的应用内交易<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-small-business-program-15-percent-112259064.html"><ins>中抽取了 30% 的分成</ins></a>。</p><p>移动平台持有者迅速将<em>《堡垒之夜》</em>从各自的应用商店下架，Epic 对<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/fortnite-google-play-lawsuit-035741548.html"><ins>他们</ins></a><a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/fortnite-maker-epic-games-sues-apple-195415590.html"><ins>提起诉讼</ins></a>，法律诉讼仍在继续。 Google 案件（<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/match-group-sues-google-225719753.html"><ins>Match Group</ins></a>作为原告参与其中）将于今年 11 月<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/epic-match-google-antitrust-lawsuit-trial-date-223014942.html#:~:text=Both%20Epic%20and%20Match%20accuse,demanding%20%244.7%20billion%20in%20damages."><ins>开庭审理</ins></a>。</p><p>无论美国发生什么，苹果和谷歌已经被迫在某些市场（例如<a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-now-allows-third-party-payments-for-apps-in-south-korea-120524308.html"><ins>韩国</ins></a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-tweaks-third-party-dating-app-payment-dutch-regulators-order-155145831.html"><ins>荷兰）</ins></a>向第三方支付系统开放其平台。另据报道，苹果计划<a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-third-party-app-stores-report-195840839.html"><ins>最快明年</ins></a>在 iPhone 上允许第三方应用商店，这在很大程度上是为了遵守即将出台的欧盟规则。 Epic 已经为此做好了准备，因为它自己的移动应用商店已<a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.axios.com/2023/03/09/epic-games-store-tim-sweeney-2023">准备就绪</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/epic-loses-bid-to-make-apple-change-its-app-store- payment-rules-right-now-174924222.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/epic-loses-bid-to-make-apple-change-its-app-store-payment-rules-right-now-174924222.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a6623aaf-8957-42e4-9f3e-701ebc830b1e</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:49:24 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691603366</ingested><modified> 2023-08-09T17:49:48+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mobile Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="2184" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-04/f83f5a40-a7b6-11eb-b97f-1ec9ee0319dd" width="3312"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2184" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-04/f83f5a40-a7b6-11eb-b97f-1ec9ee0319dd" width="3312"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - This March 19, 2018 file photo shows Apple's App Store app. Epic Games said Wednesday Feb. 17, 2021, it filed an antitrust complaint against Apple with European Union regulators, opening up a new front in its war with the tech giant over app store payments. (AP Photo/Patrick Semansky, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Europe Epic Games Apple]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Twitter fined for belatedly complying with search warrant for Donald Trump's account]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>作为对 2020 年 1 月 6 日事件调查的一部分，特别检察官杰克·史密斯 (Jack Smith) 获得了对前总统唐纳德·特朗普 (Donald Trump) 的 Twitter 帐户的搜查令。在详细说明搜查令的法庭文件浮出水面后， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.politico.com/news/2023/08/09/special-counsel-obtained-search-warrant-for-donald-trumps-twitter-account-00110484"><em>Politico</em></a>最先报道了该搜查令。</p><p>史密斯在一月份获得了搜查令，但无法从 Twitter 获取记录。首先，他的调查人员显然遇到了一个“不起作用”的网站，该网站通常用于执法部门提出法律请求。根据<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://storage.courtlistener.com/recap/gov.uscourts.cadc.39513/gov.uscourts.cadc.39513.1208541751.0.pdf">法庭记录</a>，在他们能够送达逮捕令后，推特反应缓慢。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>根据新近公开的法庭文件，该问题是一项保密协议，该协议禁止 Twitter 披露逮捕令的存在，包括向特朗普披露。该公司辩称，根据第一修正案，它有权将逮捕令通知特朗普，这导致 Twitter 和特别检察官办公室之间持续了数月的法律纠纷。</p><p>法院站在政府一边，推特被要求交出数据。在诉讼期间，政府修改了保密令，允许推特“通知前总统逮捕令的存在和内容”，前提是他们隐瞒了案件代理人的身份。</p><p>但该公司错过了法院规定的交出所有记录的最后期限，并因藐视法庭而被罚款 35 万美元。文件称：“尽管 Twitter 最终遵守了搜查令，但该公司直到法院规定的截止日期三天后才完全提供所要求的信息。”</p><p>这场法律纠纷凸显了特朗普的推特账户在 1 月 6 日事件中所扮演的角色。在骚乱当晚，@realdonaldtrump 在<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-suspends-donald-trump-001400097.html">推特上发布了对暴力暴徒的支持</a>后，该公司暂停了他的账户。去年埃隆·马斯克收购该公司后，特朗普的账户得到恢复，但这位前总统尚未重返该平台。</p><p>该公司（现称为 X）没有立即回应置评请求。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.